Singer Silas Nwachukwu Marshal aka Highlife Soes, has stated music legends like Fela and others inspired his career. Soes, who in a recent chat described his childhood experiences as interesting, said he began singing at a very young age, adding the likes of Fela, Keith Richards and several others inspired him. He explained staying in Abuja and Port-Harcourt exposed him to learning different things. “I grew up among different people and cultures. I lived and attended primary and secondary education both in Abuja and Port-Harcourt respectively. So it was quite interesting learning different things, because those moments really matter to me.   One year after viral burial Obi Cubana eulogises mom     There’s still hope for Nigeria – Davido     Story of Jesus death, resurrection manipulative – Amber Rose   “I started singing while I was young and grew up listening to different artistes but my mentors remain Keith Richards, Terry G, Fela, Ty Dolla Sign,” he stated. The “Murderer” singer further noted he is working on his next project and hopes to share it soon. “I am working on a new single and a couple of other songs but I will let the cat out of the bag it the time is due,” he added.